            "answer_text": "No, SSDs do not have unlimited reads. For that matter, I can\u2019t think of any computer part that has unlimited anything. Back to SSDs, when they reach their limits of their memory endurance, it\u2019s not correct to say it becomes a read-only drive. The memory cells that reach their limit become unusable and your data stored in those cells is then at risk, both reading and writing. Source: The SSD Endurance Experiment: They're all dead ",
